Business Rules:
A driver can take many deliveries, but each delivery only has one driver
A driver can take many orders, but each order only has one driver
A vehicle can carry many deliveries, but there is only one car per delivery
A location can have multiple orders, but an order can only have one location
A restaurant can make many orders, but an order can only be made by one restaurant
The driver gets a delivery time for each delivery they make
A restaurant may or may not have their own website
When a driver is hired to make deliveries, the day they start is registered
For every one delivery, there can be one rating
All Ids should be positive numbers
 
Unique column values — in a particular column, values may not be repeated.
No missing values — in a particular column, all rows must have known values.
Delete cascade — when a row is deleted, automatically delete all related rows.
